# scihub.conf.example
#
# Only relevant when the binary is built with `--features scihub` (off by default).
#
# Copy to ~/.config/research/scihub.conf to add extra Sci-Hub mirror hosts to probe.
# Your hosts are merged with (and take priority over) the compiled-in seed list, then
# each is live-probed with a canary DOI; only working hosts are cached and used.
#
# Format: one bare host per line, '#' comments. Scheme and slashes are stripped, so
# both "https://sci-hub.xx/" and "sci-hub.xx" work. Domains rotate under legal
# pressure — add a currently-working one here and run `research scihub-domains --refresh`.

# sci-hub.se
# sci-hub.st
# sci-hub.ru
